local_desc: You leaf through the stack of papers. You realize you don't find rocks particularly interesting. You put the papers down...

name: QUESTITEM_HEAVY_MORTAR
local_desc: The kind you build walls with. It's pretty heavy.

name: QUESTITEM_HEAVY_CRATE
local_desc: Big wooden boxes, mainly for the shipment of solid goods.

local_desc: Big wooden barrels, mainly for the shipment of liquids, grains and the like.

name: QUESTITEM_LIGHT_FUR
local_desc: Useful for keeping warm. Stinks to high heaven.

name: QUESTITEM_LIGHT_PATROLROUTE
local_desc: Orders for fresh patrol routes around the King's various territories.

name: QUESTITEM_HEAVY_MOONSHINE
local_name: Delivery: Geoff the Brigand's All-Natural Enriched Moonshine
local_desc: "Guaranteed free of unnatural flavourings, colourings or preservatives", according to the label.

name: QUESTITEM_LIGHT_KITTENS
local_desc: Someone has stitched "NOT TOO B THRON IN RIVAR" on the side.

name: QUESTITEM_LIGHT_OLDCLOTHES
local_desc: A big pile of old clothes, barely used. Probably fashionable once upon a time.

name: QUESTITEM_HEAVY_FARMTOOLS
local_desc: Tools suitable both for shoeing hooves and preparing delicious cheese-based dishes.

name: QUESTITEM_LIGHT_ASSASSINATION
local_desc: Order for the assassination of a key enemy figure. Comes with the Royal stamp.

name: QUESTITEM_LIGHT_CASUALTIES
local_desc: Lists all the casualties experienced by a unit in the past week. There's quite a lot...

name: QUESTITEM_LIGHT_RINGS
local_desc: Rings used to identify military leaders who otherwise could not be identified after battle.

name: QUESTITEM_HEAVY_MEDICAL
local_desc: A large quantity of military-issue medical supplies. Somebody is expecting trouble...

name: QUESTITEM_HEAVY_FIREBARREL
local_desc: The warnings plastered all over the outside make it abundantly clear that these barrels do not contain anything mundane. The cumulative effect of all the instructions is that they should not be touched, moved or looked at, ever.

name: QUESTITEM_TOKEN_ARENA_UNRANKED

name: QUESTITEM_TOKEN_EVENT_HALLOWEEN_2017

name: QUESTITEM_TOKEN_EVENT_EASTER_2018

An egg-shaped chunk of pyrite. Normally found deep underground, these eggs surface once per year all over Albion, making them highly valuable to certain collectors. 
Trade them in at the Vanity Merchant!

local_desc: Albion oxen are tough, and sturdy enough to carry large quantities of goods, but cannot match the pace of the continent's horses.

local_desc: Oxen are commonly used for transporting large quantities of items in Albion, as they are slow but are not easily stopped.

name: T4_MOUNT_GIANTSTAG
local_desc: Stags are fast and strong, making them favored mounts of gatherers and couriers.

name: T6_MOUNT_DIREWOLF
local_desc: One of Albion's fastest mounts, the Direwolf specializes in hunting, pursuit, and evasion.

name: T8_MOUNT_MAMMOTH_TRANSPORT
local_desc: What a mammoth lacks in speed, it makes up for in enormous carrying capacity. Mammoths are the favored transport of anyone wishing to move really, really large quantities of goods.

name: T5_MOUNT_MOABIRD_FW_BRIDGEWATCH
local_desc: Mount - A special breed originally from the steppe around Bridgewatch

name: T5_MOUNT_DIREBEAR_FW_FORTSTERLING
local_desc: Mount - A special breed originally from the mountains around Fort Sterling

name: T5_MOUNT_DIREBOAR_FW_LYMHURST
local_desc: Mount - A special breed originally from the forests around Lymhurst

name: T5_MOUNT_RAM_FW_MARTLOCK
local_desc: Mount - A special breed originally from the highlands around Martlock

name: T5_MOUNT_SWAMPDRAGON_FW_THETFORD
local_desc: Mount - A special breed originally from the swamps around Thetford

name: T8_MOUNT_MAMMOTH_BATTLE@1
local_desc: Battle Mount - This war mammoth's command platform allows its rider to direct and bolster allies. Immune to crowd control.

name: T7_MOUNT_SWAMPDRAGON_BATTLE
local_desc: Battle Mount - This mount can breathe fire on enemies and ignite them from a distance. Immune to displacement effects.

name: T7_MOUNT_ARMORED_SWAMPDRAGON_BATTLE
local_desc: Battle Mount - This armored mount can lunge at enemies and poison them. Immune to displacement effects.

name: T6_MOUNT_SIEGE_BALLISTA
local_desc: Battle Mount - Immune to displacement effects.

name: T8_MOUNT_HORSE_UNDEAD@1
local_desc: Secret rituals allow the spirit of an ancient knight's mount to animate the cooling corpse of a sacrificial horse. Loyal and obedient, its appearance nevertheless strikes fear into its foes.

name: T5_MOUNT_COUGAR_KEEPER@1
local_desc: Keeper scouts have used these fast animals to scout the wilds and will never surrender a cub willingly.

name: T8_MOUNT_COUGAR_KEEPER@1
local_desc: The fastest and most aggressive swiftclaw cubs are raised as rageclaws: battle mounts for berserker cavalry. Raised from birth to tolerate the fury of battle, rageclaws deliver their riders right into the heart of the enemy ranks.

name: T8_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE_MORGANA@1
local_desc: Every Morgana horse-breeder dreams of birthing a foal angry and aggressive enough to survive demonic possession. The resulting creature is almost as dangerous to its rider as it is to its enemies.

name: UNIQUE_MOUNT_RAM_XMAS
local_desc: Mount - With this mount you can celebrate the Midwinter Festival

name: T7_MOUNT_SWAMPDRAGON_AVALON_BASILISK
local_desc: A Swamp Dragon infused with Avalonian Energy. Can discharge energy to escape from attackers.

name: UNIQUE_MOUNT_BAT_TELLAFRIEND
local_desc: Referral Mount - Can fly on its own, though with a human on top it becomes too heavy to fly over obstacles.

name: UNIQUE_MOUNT_GIANTTOAD_02_TELLAFRIEND
local_desc: Mount - Her name is Berta. Born in a backwater swamp, she dreams of someday seeing the world.

name: T5_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE_SKIN_01
local_desc: An armored horse bearing the impressive banner of its rider's guild. Ideal for raising morale in big battles.

name: T6_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE_SKIN_01

name: UNIQUE_MOUNT_BAT_PERSONAL

name: T7_MOUNT_MONITORLIZARD_ADC
local_desc: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - Quick and hard to catch, this baleful creature can emit intoxicating poison when threatened.

name: T7_MOUNT_HUSKY_ADC
local_desc: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - A very good sprinter with a positive and loyal attitude towards humans.

name: T6_MOUNT_FROSTRAM_ADC
